# Fluff Date: 2026-02-16 11:04:06
overview:<p>The Jade Phoenix is an 85-ton Clan assault OmniMech introduced in 3148 by Clan Jade Falcon's CJF Factory Zone 4 on Alyina. Developed alongside the lighter Ion Sparrow and Hierofalcon, the Jade Phoenix was conceived as part of a new generation of partial wing-equipped OmniMechs designed to embody the Clan's warrior traditions. The design team drew inspiration from the legendary Falcon hero Aidan Pryde, seeking to create a platform that would inspire MechWarriors to embrace honorable combat over the brutal excesses of the Mongol Doctrine. Each chassis reportedly incorporates a single milligram grain of armor salvaged from Pryde's Timber Wolf, destroyed during the Battle of Tukayyid in 3052. While the veracity of this claim remains unverified, its psychological impact on pilots is undeniable, as many believe they carry the spirit of the Jade Phoenix himself into battle.</p>

capabilities:<p>The Jade Phoenix is built on a JF 8 Light Endo-Composite chassis powered by a JF 340 XL fusion engine, giving the eighty-five-ton OmniMech a respectable top speed of 64 kilometers per hour. Compound JF Ferro-Fibrous armor provides substantial protection, while a fixed Partial Wing assembly grants enhanced maneuverability that allows the design to reach positions typically inaccessible to assault-class 'Mechs. With 37 tons of available pod space, the Jade Phoenix offers commanders considerable flexibility in tailoring configurations to specific mission requirements.</p><p>The Primary configuration emphasizes long-range fire support, mounting a pair of ER PPCs alongside a devastating Hyper-Assault Gauss Rifle 30. Four pod-mounted jump jets further exploit the Partial Wing's capabilities, enabling the Jade Phoenix to seize elevated firing positions and leverage its ranged weaponry to maximum effect. Five additional double heat sinks manage the considerable thermal output of this weapons package. The straightforward armament philosophy that characterizes all configurations reflects a deliberate design choice favoring honest engagements that reward a warrior's skill over technological surprise or deception.</p><p>The XL engine represents the design's primary vulnerability, as critical hits to either side torso can prove catastrophic. However, the combination of speed, jump capability, and the Partial Wing's enhanced atmospheric performance gives skilled pilots the tools to mitigate this weakness through superior positioning.</p>

deployment:<p>Alternate Configuration C adopts a mixed missile loadout that provides exceptional tactical flexibility. Dual ATM 12 launchers with six tons of ammunition offer variable engagement capability through their multiple munition types, while paired SRM 6 racks add concentrated short-range firepower. Two ER medium lasers provide energy backup, and a pair of talons give this configuration a uniquely dangerous physical attack capability that can surprise opponents expecting a purely ranged engagement. Four jump jets round out the package, and the combination of missile flexibility and melee capability makes the C configuration well-suited to fluid battlefield conditions where engagement ranges shift rapidly.</p>

history:<p>The Jade Phoenix emerged from CJF Factory Zone 4 on Alyina in 3148, the last of three new OmniMech designs to enter production following the Ion Sparrow in 3147 and the Hierofalcon earlier that same year. All three designs featured the distinctive partial wing systems that had become a hallmark of Alyina's engineering output, but the Jade Phoenix carried an additional burden of symbolism. Its creators, scientists and technicians of the civilian caste, took the unusual step of openly attempting to shape warrior culture by designing a 'Mech intended to reconnect Clan Jade Falcon with the heroic traditions of its past rather than the destructive impulses championed by Khan Malvina Hazen.</p><p>This philosophical stance ensured that the Jade Phoenix found its strongest support among Falcon warriors who rejected the Mongol Doctrine. The OmniMech became most commonly deployed in Clusters that favored traditional combat, particularly those within the Delta and Zeta Galaxies. Pro-Malvina elements within the Clan's touman viewed the design with open disdain, preferring the raptor-styled totem 'Mechs manufactured by Olivetti Weaponry and Eagle Craft Group that emphasized predatory aggression over noble bearing.</p><p>The Jade Phoenix proved its combat worth during the Battle of Skye in March 3150, where it demonstrated particular effectiveness in single combat during Trials of Grievance. The design's straightforward armament and superior maneuverability made it a formidable dueling platform, and traditional Falcon warriors frequently chose the Jade Phoenix for combat trials as a deliberate repudiation of the Mongol Doctrine's emphasis on overwhelming force.</p><p>Following Khan Malvina Hazen's ill-fated expedition to Terra and the subsequent upheaval within Clan Jade Falcon, the political landscape surrounding the Jade Phoenix shifted dramatically. The newly formed Alyina Mercantile League assumed control of CJF Factory Zone 4, and the Jade Phoenix became available to mercenary forces hired by the League. This commercialization marked a significant departure from the design's original purpose as a symbol of Falcon honor, though the 'Mech's reputation for reliable, straightforward performance has made it an attractive acquisition for mercenary commands seeking a capable assault platform.</p>

